    "Collecting these responses is essential for eliciting mechanisms (see section 2.2), as well as for verifying the experiments are working as intended (e.g.",
    "seeing whether an agent is embodying an assigned role).",
    "Interventions: These are isolated changes to any element of the game environment or the agents themselves.",
    "With GABE, it becomes possible to pull levers that are not normally available in real-world lab experiments, such as manipulating an agent's preferences or tolerance for risk.",
